    • onActivate

      protected abstract void onActivate()

      Abstract method that is executed after this Content is set as the active contnet.

      Details

      1. This method is executed by the Toolbox Executor.
      2. The onDeactivate() implementation of the previous content is executed prior to this method.
        • That said, because both operations are executed in a separate execution, the operations are very likely to occur concurrently.
        • The only exception to this rule is if the Executor is limited to a single background thread.
        • However, even then, both operations will always be executed concurrently with remaining JavaFX operations taking place in the ContentManager.onChange(Content, Content) method.
      3. This method is wrapped in the onSetInternal() method.
